    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 5,
        "Tafseer": "\"Have he made the gods [only] one God? Indeed, this is a curious thing.\" (5)\n\nThe Malicious Propaganda of the Quraysh\n\nAlong with the Prophet's (pbuh) claim to prophethood, the second thing with which the leaders of the Quraysh had the greatest conflict was his invitation to Tawhid. Using this, they incited their common people against him. Since every tribe had different idols and every tribe held blind devotion to its idol, they, to incite tribal bias, spread this malicious propaganda: 'This person has ended all deities to make only one deity; what can be more strange than this!' Reflect on this phrase, as it contains two poisons. First, this person has ended the divinity of all deities except the one whom he himself accepts as deity. Second, this is an action which is highly unique, having no parallel in the history of our ancestors. The word 'ujab' (curious) contains the meaning of exaggeration compared to 'ajeeb' (strange). If you reflect, this propaganda was sufficient to incite the entire Arab nation against the Prophet (pbuh), but Allah Almighty protected His Prophet from its evil."
    },
