        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 6,
        "Tafseer": "\"And the prominent among them went forth, [saying], 'Go and be steadfast to your gods. Indeed, this is a thing intended.'\" (6)\n\nA Depiction of the Leaders' Attitude\n\nThis is a depiction of the attitude which the leaders of the Quraysh adopted to turn people away from the Prophet's (pbuh) invitation to Tawhid. Whenever they saw that people were being influenced by the Prophet's (pbuh) word, they would depart from there and also incite others: 'Depart from here, do not listen to this person's words, but remain steadfast in the worship of your deities.'\n\n'Indeed, this is a thing intended'—meaning: the primary task to be done is that this person is trying to turn you away from your ancestral religion with this sermon. In contrast, the task to be done, which should be desired by everyone among us, is that despite all his efforts, we remain steadfast in the worship of our deities until the end."
