        "AyahNumber": 8,
        "Tafseer": "\"Has the message been revealed to him out of [all of] us?\" Rather, they are in doubt of My message. Rather, they have not yet tasted My punishment. (8)\n\nStriking at the Arrogance of the Quraysh\n\nThat is, they say in the arrogance of their leadership and wealth: 'If God had to send down a Book upon any human, did He find only him (Muhammad [pbuh]) among us? If Allah Almighty had willed to do this, He would have chosen one of the chiefs of Makkah or Ta'if for this, not a poor and resourceless man like him upon whom his companions are poor and resourceless people like him.' This is the expression of their arrogance which was mentioned at the beginning of the Surah with the words 'fi 'izzatin' (in pride). To strike at this arrogance of theirs, He stated: 'Rather, they are in doubt of My message'—meaning all these claims of theirs are because they are still in doubt regarding the punishment of which they are being warned in this Qur'an, considering it merely an empty threat. The reason is that it has not appeared before them yet, and these people are not convinced merely by proofs, but are those who believe after seeing everything with their eyes. The meaning is: today they are being made to understand with proofs, but if they do not understand, ultimately the whip of punishment will also appear before them."
