    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 9,
        "Tafseer": "\"Or do they have the depositories of the mercy of your Lord, the Exalted in Might, the Giver?\" (9)\n\nReply to Their Arrogance\n\nThis is a reply to that arrogance of theirs which was pointed to in the preceding verse—showing that they are carefree regarding God's grasp relying on their own wealth! Look at them, what is their reality! Have they assumed that Allah Almighty has handed over the keys to all His treasures to them so that they may give to whomever they please and keep whomever they please deprived? Thus, it is beyond their understanding how Allah Almighty could make anyone outside their circle the holder of prophethood, messengership, and the Qur'an. They do not know that Allah Almighty is 'Al-Aziz' (the Exalted in Might) and 'Al-Wahhab' (the Giver)—meaning the sole Owner and Dispenser of all His treasures without any partner, and the Giver. He bestows generously upon those of His servants who, though they appear of no worth in their eyes, hold a great status in the sight of God; thus, while He has given them some of the broken pieces of clay of this earth over which they are boasting, He has blessed whomever He willed with the kingdom of prophethood, messengership, knowledge, and wisdom, than which no greater office can be conceived."
