        "Tafseer": "\"[They are but] a defeated soldiers of the [defeating] companies.\" (11)\n\nEven the Greatest Power of the World Cannot Face God's Punishment\n\nThe referent of 'Hunalika' (there) is that very punishment which was mentioned in verse 8 with the words: 'they have not yet tasted My punishment'. The meaning is: if these people are waiting for the manifestation of God's punishment to believe, then they should remember that when that punishment comes, no great army of any nation will be able to stand against it; rather, it will necessarily be defeated. The indefiniteness (tankeer) of 'Jund' (soldier/army) is to magnify its status, and 'ma' is to emphasize this indefiniteness—meaning whatever army it may be, and whatever power and glory it may possess, it cannot stand against the punishment of God."
