    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 14,
        "Tafseer": "\"Each of them did not but deny the messengers, so My penalty was justified.\" (14)\n\nThat is, the primary crime of every one of them was that they denied Allah's messengers, and you are also committing this very crime. 'Fahaqqa 'iqab' (so My penalty was justified) is originally 'fahaqqa 'iqabi' (so My penalty was justified upon them), where the final 'ya' is dropped to observe the rhyme, just as it was dropped in 'lamayadhaqoo 'adhab' in verse 8.\n\n'Fawag' means interval and respite.\n\n'Qitt' means portion and share.\n\nDemanding the Punishment and Its Reply\n\nThis points to the Quraysh—stating: these people are demanding the punishment with great pomp, as if they have constructed an impregnable defense line against it, whereas a single shout of God will be sufficient to destroy them, and a second will not even be needed, and His grasp will be such that they will not get even a moment's respite."
