    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 16,
        "Tafseer": "\"And they say, 'Our Lord, hasten for us our share [of punishment] before the Day of Account.'\" (16)\n\nThis describes their arrogance in demanding the punishment—showing that in the heat of denying the Prophet (pbuh), they went to the extent of saying: 'O our Lord! If this person is truthful in his claim that we will face punishment for denying him, then let that punishment come upon us before the Day of Judgment so that his truthfulness is proven. If he is truthful, and (God forbid) his lie is proven if he is a liar, as we assume.' This demand of the Quraysh has also passed in Surah Al-Anfal in these words:\n\n'And [remember] when they said, \"O Allah, if this should be the truth from You, then rain down upon us stones from the sky or bring us a painful punishment.\"' (32)\n\nIt is also narrated from Abu Jahl regarding the Day of Badr that he supplicated: 'O God, whoever among us has been the cause of severing family ties—to the extent that the sword of the Quraysh is drawn against the Quraysh themselves—destroy him tomorrow!'"
