        "AyahNumber": 18,
        "Tafseer": "\"Indeed, We subjected the mountains [to praise] with him, exalting [Allah] in the afternoon and the morning. And the birds: assembled, all to Him repeatedly turning.\" (18-19)\n\nHazrat Dawud's Devotion\n\nThis explains Hazrat Dawud's (peace be upon him) devotion—showing that in the evening and morning, sitting in the lap of the mountains, he performed the glorification of his Lord, and when he sang the verses of the Psalms (Zabur) in his special melody, the mountains also harmonized with him and the birds also gathered in groups to join their voices with his. Allah Almighty had placed such influence in his melody and his tender heart that the entire atmosphere around him resonated with his voice, and mountains, beasts, and birds became his companions in repentance and supplication... We have clarified in its proper place that everything in this universe glorifies Allah Almighty, but we do not understand their glorification. However, our not understanding does not mean that no one understands it. Just as Allah Almighty had blessed Hazrat Dawud (peace be upon him) with a melody that melted mountains and attracted birds, He had also blessed him with a hearing ear to understand their glorification and supplications. In the previous Surahs, these matters have been clarified, so we limit our discussion to an allusion here."
