    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 46,
        "Tafseer": "\"And remember Our servants, Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, possessors of strength and [religious] vision.\" (45-46)\n\nThe Special Mission of Hazrat Ibrahim, Hazrat Ishaq, and Hazrat Yacob\n\nThis is a reminder of Hazrat Ibrahim (peace be upon him), Hazrat Ishaq (peace be upon him), and Hazrat Yacob (peace be upon him). These are the founders of the Israelite line of guidance and reform. These people possessed ancestral leadership and also spiritual vision. For this reason, their attribute is mentioned as 'possessors of strength and [religious] vision'—meaning Allah Almighty had blessed them with power and vision. If power is not accompanied by vision, a person becomes a highly dangerous animal. It states: We chose them for the special mission of reminding of the Hereafter, and they were among Our chosen and righteous ones.\n\n'the remembrance of the home' (Dhikra ad-Dar) serves as an appositive (badal) to 'khalisatan' (sincere/pure), and 'home' refers to the home of the Hereafter, because the actual home is that alone. This world is merely a transient inn. The primary work of the honorable Prophets (peace be upon them) is, in reality, to remind of the Hereafter, because the remembrance of the Hereafter is the key to all reform and success. If man is negligent of it, he falls into the trap of Satan. And if its remembrance remains alive within him, he remains on the straight path despite lapses."
    },
