    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 55,
        "Tafseer": "\"This [for the righteous]. But indeed, for the transgressors is an evil place of return -\" (55)\n\nThe Punishment of the Rebellious\n\nThat is, on one hand, for the God-fearing will be these blessings and honors, and on the other hand, for the transgressors and rebellious will be an evil place of return. 'Transgressors' (Tagheen) refers to those very people who were mentioned at the beginning of the Surah with the words: 'But those who disbelieve are in pride and dissension'—meaning those who, instead of turning to God, mock His reminder and dispute with His messenger."
    },
    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 56,
        "Tafseer": "\"Hell, which they will [enter to] burn, and wretched is the resting place.\" (56)\n\nThis explains that evil place of return—meaning this evil place is Hell. 'they will [enter to] burn'—meaning they will not be shown Hell from a distance, but they will have to enter it, and wretched is the resting place they will enter!"
    },
    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 57,
        "Tafseer": "\"This - so let them taste it - is boiling water and purulence And other [punishments] of its type [in various] pairs.\" (57-58)\n\n'This - so let them taste it - is boiling water and purulence'—'Hameem' refers to boiling water, and 'Ghassaq' means purulence. They will be told: 'These things are here, taste them.' After this, mentioning two of these disgusting things, He stated that there will be other various disgusting things of the same type, which are not worthy of being mentioned. It should be kept in mind here that these things will be given to the people of Hell as a first hospitality (nuzul), as is clarified in verse 62. The actual punishment will begin after this."
