    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 69,
        "Tafseer": "\"I had no knowledge of the exalted assembly when they were disputing. It has not been revealed to me except that I am a clear warner.\" (69-70)\n\nThat is, do not remain in the misconception that I am presenting myself as a clear warner merely to overawe you, and am narrating the fable of the bickering of the people of Hell to frighten you. How could I have knowledge of these matters of the exalted assembly? Allah Almighty is informing me of this through His revelation so that I may warn you of the terror of the coming Day like an alerted warner. Otherwise, I am not a knower of the unseen; I am only a clear warner. 'Nadhir mubeen' has been explained in its proper place. Here, the meaning is: Allah Almighty has informed me of these events hidden behind the curtains of the future so that I may warn you of them as if they are before my eyes."
