    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 71,
        "Tafseer": "Ayah 71-74\n\nThe Genealogy of Arrogance\n\nThis describes that story of Hazrat Adam (peace be upon him) and Iblis which has been described briefly in various Surahs, and we have discussed all its aspects in detail. Particularly, it has been explained with great clarity. Here, the reference to this story is to describe the genealogy of that arrogance which was mentioned at the beginning of the Surah with the words: 'But those who disbelieve are in pride and dissension', and which has been struck throughout this Surah. It is as if the Quraysh are shown in this mirror: the pride and arrogance in which they are caught to deny the invitation of the Qur'an is the inheritance of Iblis, not of the righteous. Caught in this, he refused to prostrate to Adam (peace be upon him), as a retribution for which he was cursed. The meaning is: if they wish to revive his Sunnah, they should be prepared to face the end which Iblis and his followers will face."
    },
