    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 75,
        "Tafseer": "\"[Allah] said, 'O Iblis, what prevented you from prostrating to that which I created with My hands? Were you arrogant then, or were you [already] among the haughty?'\" (75)\n\nMan is a Masterpiece of Nature\n\nUpon Iblis's refusal to prostrate, Allah Almighty questioned him by way of anger: 'What prevented you from prostrating to that which I created with My hands? Were you arrogant then, or are you some superior creation?' 'created with My hands' (khalaqtu bi-yadayya) points to that special care which Allah Almighty showed to create man. Man, in terms of his capabilities, is a masterpiece of nature. If he uses his capabilities correctly, subduing the Jinn is an ordinary thing; he excels even the angels. The entire world is subjected to him, but he has not been made subordinate to anyone except his Lord. The meaning is: when such is the creation created with this care, and when God Himself commanded you to prostrate to it, on what basis did you refuse to prostrate? Value belongs to attributes and capabilities, not to dust and fire; if the hand of nature prepared its masterpiece from a lump of clay, will its beauty and perfection be denied on the basis that it was prepared from clay! It states: 'your action is merely the result of blind arrogance, or you assume yourself to be some superior being!'"
    },
    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 76,
        "Tafseer": "\"He said, 'I am better than him. You created me from fire and created him from clay.'\" (76)\n\nBasing Excellence on Lineage is an Invention of Satan\n\nIblis replied: 'I am better than him,' and gave the proof: 'You created me from fire and created him from clay'—meaning he claimed his superiority, and in its proof, presented the thing that his creation was from a superior element. In other words: he based excellence not on attributes, but on lineage and family. This is the very same logic which the leaders of the Quraysh presented against the Prophet (pbuh) and his poor companions, which has passed above in this Surah—stating that if Allah Almighty had to send down a Book, He would send it down upon one of us, not upon a resourceless man like him whose companions are poor and resourceless people like him."
    },
    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 77,
        "Tafseer": "Satan's Challenge and Its Reply\n\n\"[Allah] said, 'Then get out of it, for indeed, you are expelled. And indeed, upon you is My curse until the Day of Recompense.'\" (77-78)\n\nThe referent of the pronoun in 'from it' (min-ha) is Paradise. This is because this event, as is clarified in other places, occurred in Paradise. Allah Almighty, declaring him cursed after this rebellion, commanded him to get out of Paradise, and stated: 'My curse is upon you until the Day of Recompense. On that Day, you will face the punishment for this crime of yours.'"
