    {
        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 79,
        "Tafseer": "\"He said, 'My Lord, then delay me until the Day they are resurrected.' [Allah] said, 'So indeed, you are of those delayed Until the Day of the time well-known.'\" (79-81)\n\nFrom this curse of Allah Almighty, Iblis assumed that perhaps his respite was being ended and he would not be given the opportunity to show his strength against man; for this reason, he requested: 'Delay me until the Day they are raised for the reckoning of their deeds.' Allah Almighty granted him this respite."
