        "SurahNumber": 38,
        "AyahNumber": 86,
        "Tafseer": "\"Say, [O Muhammad], 'I do not ask you for it any payment, and I am not of the pretentious. It is not but a reminder to the worlds. And you will surely know [the truth of] its information after a time.'\" (86-88)\n\nWarning by Way of Advice\n\nAt the end, this is declared through the tongue of the Prophet (pbuh)—stating: 'I do not ask you any payment for this Qur'an which I am reciting to you, so that if you do not value it, I will be deprived of the payment. I have not taken up this heavy burden of my own desire, but this is a responsibility placed by God; therefore, its reward is also with Him, and He alone will also help and guide me in performing its responsibilities. If you reject it, remember that this is a great reminder from the Lord of the worlds to the people of the world, and what it is giving news of, not much time will pass before it stands manifest before you.'\n\nBy the grace of Allah, the commentary of this Surah is completed on these lines. Our final call is that all praise belongs to Allah, Lord of the worlds.\n\nRahman Abad: 21 May, 1975 AD."
